to come in and eat something?
No.

787
00:39:15,485 --> 00:39:16,974
(CHUCKLES) No, thank you.

788
00:39:22,324 --> 00:39:23,621
Take a seat right over there.

789
00:39:23,693 --> 00:39:26,786
(MEN CHATTERING)

790
00:39:29,099 --> 00:39:30,088
MAN 1: Okay.

791
00:39:31,601 --> 00:39:34,297
Peter called.
He's going to be late.
He said to start without him.

792
00:39:35,038 --> 00:39:37,335
Oh, well, come on
then, let's play.
That's what we're here for.

793
00:39:40,043 --> 00:39:41,032
Okay.

794
00:39:41,811 --> 00:39:43,608
MAN 2: Come on,
short, little guy.

795
00:39:44,114 --> 00:39:45,740
You're out?
This is it?

796
00:39:46,248 --> 00:39:47,510
MAN 3: Anybody else?

797
00:39:47,617 --> 00:39:49,050
You're still in?

798
00:39:49,152 --> 00:39:52,349
So sorry, old chaps.
I was completely
bogged down at the office.

799
00:39:52,422 --> 00:39:53,581
Okay.

800
00:39:53,655 --> 00:39:54,884
All right, who's winning?

801
00:39:54,958 --> 00:39:56,858
Mr. Spence
is a good poker player, Peter.

802
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:58,483
Yes, I might have known.

803
00:39:58,628 --> 00:40:02,688
Actually,
I bought my first Reuben's
with poker winnings.

804
00:40:03,032 --> 00:40:04,829
You bought a Rubens painting?

805
00:40:05,367 --> 00:40:07,460
Not a painting.
A sandwich.

806
00:40:08,371 --> 00:40:09,702
I could use a drink.

807
00:40:10,106 --> 00:40:12,768
He asked me
if I believed in love
at first sight.

808
00:40:12,842 --> 00:40:14,775
(EXCLAIMS)
How sweet is that?
So naive.

809
00:40:14,844 --> 00:40:16,208
Well, I hope
you told him yes.

810
00:40:16,278 --> 00:40:17,768
I told him
we had nothing in common.

811
00:40:17,847 --> 00:40:20,007
We come from
completely different
backgrounds.

812
00:40:20,083 --> 00:40:21,606
I think
he likes that or something.

813
00:40:21,684 --> 00:40:25,483
But what about the story
you're writing on him?
What is that all about?

814
00:40:28,891 --> 00:40:29,983
Sondra?

815
00:40:35,798 --> 00:40:38,699
"Mary Thompson,
a short-haired brunette,

816
